			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I've never ever seen any instance where healing a summoned pet gets you on the hatelist. But there are nearly infinite ways to accidentally get on the hatelist when dealing with KoS mobs - you're sitting during the pull for a moment, some other mob aggroes and the other one then gets assist aggro, etc.
<br />

<br />
No beneficial spells cast on a summoned pet add any amount of hate whatsoever to mobs that have the pet on their hatelist.
<br />

<br />
If anyone can show me a reproducable scenario where a non-KoS mob aggroes on someone for healing/buffing a summoned pet tanking this mob, I'll hand over all my droppable possessions to this person. It's simply impossible, so there's nothing I have to worry about. Anyone up for the task?<br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=597626">Enharjaren Fenrirsbane</a>  - retired, please don't laugh at my obsolete gear.
<br />
Arch Overseers
<br />
Bristlebane
<br />

<br />
Fruktan - Tauren shaman on Test 1
